==== The Alchemical Operations

*Distillation*

- Most common use in herbal alchemy: steam distillation of essential oils (Sulfur) and distillation of fermented alcohol (Mercury).
- *Rectification:* Repeated distillation of alcohol (6–12 times) to increase purity and spiritual elevation. Pure 100% alcohol cannot be obtained by distillation alone — maximum ~95% unless a drying agent is used (potassium carbonate or quicklime/calcium oxide).
- Types: simple, fractional, steam, vacuum, solar, etc.

#lab[
  *Solar Distillation (simplest):* Place liquid in a small jar inside a larger sealed jar in a sunny spot. Distillate condenses on the walls and runs down to be collected at the bottom.
]

*Digestion*

- Allowing matter to incubate at constant temperature for a period of time. Temperature may be slowly increased. Described as "hatching an egg." — "The whole of the Art is a controlled digestion."
- Common temperature: ~40°C.

*Sublimation*

- A solid passes directly to vapor without a liquid state; vapor deposits as solid on a cool surface.
- Many ammonia-based salts purified this way.

#lab[
  *Easy sublimation setup:* Layer material on the bottom of a Corning Ware casserole; invert a second casserole on top. Gently heat the bottom. Sublimate collects on the upper surfaces. Temperature range: near room temperature to full red heat depending on subject.
]

*Circulation*

- Continuous distillation to evolve matter. Subject is placed in a tall bottle and gently heated at the bottom while the top remains cool — liquid distils upward, condenses, falls back. Often run for a month or longer. Many life/death/rebirth cycles occur.
- Steps from simple Spagyric into truly alchemical preparation.

#lab[
  *Easy circulation setup:* Tall wine bottle filled with 3–4 oz of liquid, set on a warm heating pad.
]

*Calcination*

- Apply fire to produce a white ash — burns off volatile structural components, reveals the essential mineral Salt.

#lab[
  *Easy method:* Burn extracted herb residue outdoors in a fire-resistant dish (avoid aluminum). Touch match, stir occasionally. Grind ash; calcine further to light gray.

  *Leaching process (Salt of Salt):* Mix gray ash with 10–20× its volume of distilled water. Stir; heat near boiling; filter. Evaporate the liquid → white crystalline *Salt of Salt*. The undissolved residue is *Caput Mortuum* (Dead Head / Terra Damnata — discarded).

  *Salt of Sulfur:* Take fermentation liquor (after alcohol removed) or alcohol extract; evaporate to thick honey-like mass; calcine. Wet with distilled water or plant phlegm; calcine again repeatedly until light gray/white. Leach as above → *Salt of Sulfur* (a magnet for the subtle Sulfur principle).
]

*Solve et Coagula*

- Ancient formula for exalting matter. Dissolve salts into water; filter; evaporate to dryness → recrystallization. Passing matter through the life/death/rebirth cycle.
- In the liquid state, materials are most susceptible to astrological influence (especially the Moon).
- *Phlegm:* Water that distils over when continuing distillation of fermented liquid after alcohol removal, down to the honey-like residue. Best solvent for purifying salts of the same plant. Keep it.

