=== Chapter Six: Herbal Alchemy

==== The Magisteries

#doctrine[
  Paracelsus: 1 part Magistery has the same effect as 200 parts of the corresponding dried plant.
]

#lab[
  *Magistery Process (Paracelsus):*
  1. Chop fresh plant; cover with rectified spirit of wine (any strong potable alcohol). Digest sealed at ~40°C for 1 month.
  2. Gently distil to dryness in water bath (do not burn). Pour distillate over fresh herb; digest 1 month; distil again.
  3. Repeat digestion–distillation with fresh herb until distillate volume = 5× the original alcohol volume (e.g., 100 mL → 500 mL).
  4. Circulate the final distillate for 1 month.
  5. The Magistery collects as oily-looking drops — either sinking or floating depending on the herb. Collect with dropper into sealed vial.
  - Seven magisteries (one per planet/day) parallel the Seven Basics.
