#lab[
  *Collecting Rainwater (best in spring, Sun in Aries–Taurus–Gemini; thundershowers preferred — lightning fixes more nitrogen):*
  - Rain must NOT touch metal, earth, plants, or animals/humans.
  - Stake plastic sheeting; lead runoff into plastic bucket. Filter all collected water.
  - Cover with cloth (breathes but keeps dust out). Place in warm spot (30–40°C) to ferment for at least 1 month (1 year+ is better).
  - Result: white to brownish solid-like tufts of cotton floating in water = *Universal Gur* (Seed of Nature).

  *3-Fraction Distillation of the Gur:*
  1. Gently sweat over the first quarter of volume → *Fire and Air of Water* (label and save).
  2. Raise temperature; distil most of the water (not to dryness) → *Water of Water* (label and save).
  3. Residue slowly dried in Sun → *Earth of Water* (contains the Universal Gur).
