=== Chapter Eight: Return to the Fire

==== The Grades of Fire

#doctrine[
  "Fire is the primary agent, that of the whole Art. It is the first of the Four Elements." — Olympiodorus (~500 C.E.)
]

- *Celestial Fire* (most subtle): The One Only Thing. Undivided Light. Not burning but gentle, invisible, known only by its operations. Source of all other fires. Visible representative = the Sun. Also called: Universal Fire, Astral Gold, Divine Will.
  - The "Sun behind the Sun" — our visible star is condensed Celestial Fire.
  - *Universal aspect:* Diffused everywhere; excites movement in bodies; warms and preserves the Germ of all things.
  - *Particular aspect* (Innate Fire / Central Fire): Implanted in each mixture with its Germ. Acts little unless excited.

- *Quintessence:* "Most purified and fixed part of a matter," formed by perfect balance of the Four Elements. The Fifth Element. Its action is digestive and maturing. When harmony between opposing forces of the elements is obtained, a whole new exalted state arises.

#doctrine[
  "The Seed is the Elixir or Quintessence of anything, its most perfect digestion and decoction. Or again the Balm of Sulfur, which is the same as the Radical Moisture in metals. The Four Elements by their continual action project a constant supply of seed to the center of the Earth, where it is digested, and whence it proceeds again in generative motions. This is the fountainhead of all things terrestrial." — Michael Sendivogius, The New Chymical Light (1608)
]

==== The Circulation of Fire (Fountain of Nature)

- Celestial Fire condenses → Element Air → condenses further → Element Water → condenses → Element Earth.
- Central Fire (trapped within) reverses the process: Earth volatilizes → thickened Water; Water volatilizes → vapor; Air rarifies → Fire element → regenerated by Celestial Fire. Cycle repeats.
- This perpetual circulation = *Fountain of Nature*.

#doctrine[
  "Thus Fire and Air come down into Waters and impregnate them. The Waters dispose of their thickest part and give it to the Earth. The Earth thereby becomes overloaded or saturated, which superfluity of Earth and Water is again volatilized and sublimed upwards by the Fire (Inverted Fire or Central Fire) into vapors." — The Golden Chain of Homer
]

==== The Proper Medium

#doctrine[
  "You can not move from one extreme to another extreme without the proper medium." — The Golden Chain of Homer
]

- To turn Earth into Fire you must pass through Water and Air. One Element is the conductor of those adjacent. It dissolves and subtilizes the other. Elements serve as: magnet, solvent, volatilizing, condensing, coagulating, and fixing principles for one another.

==== Rotation of the Elements

- The cyclic rotation of elements is an important key to alchemical procedure: the essence of a substance is extracted, purified, and raised to its most sublime state. With each rotation, the Four Elements come into greater balance and purity. When perfect harmony is obtained → *Quintessence*.
- "The path is not so much a circle but a corkscrew, exalting the matter and drawing the Elements to a center of balance, the pinnacle of the matter."
- _"When thou made the quadrangle round, then is all the secret found." — Ripley 1480_


