==== The Hand of the Philosophers (Five Keys)

Isaac Holland: "In the power of the salts and their preparation lies the whole art of alchemy."

*1. Niter (Potassium Nitrate, KNO₃) — The King of Salts / The Thumb*

- "He is the mill, through which everything must be ground."
- Historically obtained from specially prepared niter beds of decomposing plant/animal wastes, wood ashes, and loose soil (1–3 years). Leached with water; evaporated; recrystallized.
- Commercial KNO₃ is not Philosophical. Must be *reanimated*:
  - Minimum: recrystallize from rainwater several times, allowing absorption of air moisture between crystallizations.
  - Better: dissolve in fresh urine; crystallize from rainwater.
- "Niter is the corporified spirit of the stars, and therein is the nature of metals. Niter is the body of the stars, whose central fire or Sulfur is called Sol." — F. la Fontain, 1797

*2. Vitriol (Copper Sulfate / Iron Sulfate) — Index Finger / Six-Pointed Star*

- Old names: Atrament (blackening agent for inks and leather); Lixivium of Marcasites.
- Found near sulfide ore deposits where water leaches it from weathering ore.
- Basil Valentine: called it "The True Mineral Salt which contains the Red and the White spirits."
- Distillation alone: first comes over clear liquid (White spirit, sulfur dioxide, forms mild sulfuric acid); then more viscous reddish liquid (Red spirit = concentrated sulfuric acid filled with martial essence).
- Name: from Latin _vitrum_ (glass) — the crystals are very glassy and transparent.

#lab[
  *Making your own iron vitriol (ferrous sulfate, FeSO₄·7H₂O):*
  1. Grind 10–20 lbs of iron pyrite (FeS) to powder; spread on large flat iron tray.
  2. Alternately roast gently and spray with rainwater (moisten then dry). Repeat many times over several months.
  3. Wash weathered ore with rainwater; save all wash water; continue weathering what remains.
  4. Filter/decant wash water into wide bowl; allow to evaporate. (Add a few drops of concentrated sulfuric acid to retard air oxidation.) Collect emerald green crystals.
  5. Purify by recrystallization from rainwater → very glassy, transparent crystals.
]

*3. Sal Ammoniac (Ammonium Chloride, NH₄Cl) — The Star / Middle Finger*

- "The Spirit of all things is Sal Ammoniac."
- "Sal Ammoniac can unite all things that are antagonistic and cannot be mixed so that afterwards they mix and conjugate." — Isaac Holland
- Sublimes easily (solid → vapor of HCl + NH₃ → recombines on cool surface as solid). This corrosive atmosphere opens many metals for extraction.
- Use in sublimation with mineral/metal ores to open subtle parts; deposit with sublimate in purified form.

#lab[
  *Tincture of Silver (Fulcanelli's method):*
  1. Obtain Horn Silver (Cerargyrite, mainly AgCl) — or precipitate pure silver dissolved in nitric acid with sea salt solution (wash precipitate, dry).
  2. Mix with 3× its weight of Sal Ammoniac; grind well. Gently sublime; collect sublimate.
  3. Dissolve sublimate in rainwater; allow to settle. Red-brown fine solid (Lunar Sulfur) falls to the bottom.
  4. Decant clear liquid (save for recovering Sal Ammoniac by evaporation). Wash solids several times with rainwater; dry.
  5. Extract dried powder with rectified wine alcohol (95%+) for 1 month.
  6. Clear golden alcohol extract = *Tincture of Silver* (contains the Lunar Sulfur).
]

*4. Alum (Potassium Aluminum Sulfate, KAl(SO₄)₂) — The Lantern / Ring Finger*

- Low melting point (92.5°C): often added to assist fusion of other salts and mineral bodies.
- At high temperatures: releases sulfur oxides in large amounts → assists production of sulfuric acid.
- Uses: cleaning, deodorizing, mordant for dyes, leather preparation, astringent, styptic.
- Best natural source: *Alunite* (Alum stone) — grind, roast, dissolve in water, filter, evaporate → Alum crystals.

*5. Salt (Sodium Chloride, NaCl) — The Key / Little Finger*

- Sea salt or Sal Gemma (mined salt).

*The Fixed Spirit of Salt:*

#lab[
  1. Grind fine sea salt; dissolve in distilled vinegar from white wine. Filter into a wide bowl; gently heat to evaporate.
  2. A crust or skin forms at the surface = *Spiritus* of the salt. Collect carefully with skimmer. Continue until liquid is too small. Repeat the process (dissolve in fresh vinegar, evaporate, collect Spiritus) a second time.
  3. The remaining bowl residue = *Corpora* of the salt.
  4. To *fix* the Spiritus: recrystallize from rainwater several times. Dry; powder; add Sal Ammoniac (~1/10 total weight). Seal in tall flask; digest at least 1 month. Dry gently. Seal for use.
  - Result = *Fixed Spiritus Salis* — reported to have miraculous healing virtues.
]

==== Dissolving Waters and Mineral Acids

- Combinations of the Five Salts, distilled at high temperatures, produce *Aqua Fortis* (Strong Waters) = mineral acids.

Recipes:

- *~50% Nitric Acid (HNO₃):* Equal parts niter + vitriol + 1/3 part Alum. Distil to ~800°C. Yield ~20% by weight of solids.
- *Sulfuric Acid:* Distil vitriol alone or with Alum.
- *Hydrochloric Acid (HCl):* Concentrated sulfuric acid + common salt.
- *Aqua Regia* (dissolves gold): Modern: 3 parts HCl + 1 part HNO₃. Old method: 2 parts niter + 1 part Sal Ammoniac, distilled at high temperature. Or: 4 parts vitriol + 6 parts niter + 1 part Alum → distil; add Sal Ammoniac to distillate.
- *Dry Aqua Regia:* Mix niter + sal ammoniac as powders; add metal to be dissolved; a few drops of rainwater to start. Generates Aqua Regia slowly.

#safety[
  - *Explosive danger:* Mixtures with niter are essentially a form of gunpowder. Add material to a hot crucible slowly or risk *Detonation*. This is why the ancients called certain operations by that name.
  - Vitriol and Alum distillation involves sulfur oxides (toxic). Work outdoors or in fume hood.
  - High temperatures (400–800°C) and corrosive acids require Pyrex/porcelain/iron retorts.
  - Lye (potassium/sodium hydroxide) solutions are strongly caustic — protect eyes and skin.
  - Do not use aluminum vessels in alchemical work.
  - Some claim *borax* and *aluminum* lead to alchemical death of the subject and should be avoided entirely.
]

==== Dry Menstruum (Fusion / Alkali)

- Salts act as Dry Menstrua: total liquefaction of mineral/metal by high-temperature fusion.
- Alkali carbonates (K₂CO₃, Na₂CO₃ / Natron): fuse at ~900°C; dissolve many mineral bodies. Used extensively in glassmaking and ceramics.
- Fixed Salt of Tartar (K₂CO₃): "penetrates every metal on fusion and takes from them the Sulfurous part."

#lab[
  1. Heat large porcelain crucible; fuse Salt of Tartar until ~half full.
  2. Slowly add powdered ore (oxide form usually); allow to fuse; stir with iron rod.
  3. Continue adding ore and fresh Tartar Salt to maintain complete flux.
  4. Cool in crucible then break out, OR cast molten liquid onto smooth heat-resistant surface.
  5. Grind warm solid. Two options:
     - *Option A:* Allow powdered mass to deliquesce; extract metal's Sulfur with Kerkring Menstruum (as in Ens Tincture process).
     - *Option B:* Dissolve mass in rainwater; allow solids to settle; dry solids; extract with prepared menstruum.
]

==== Ysopaica: The Art of Washing Things White by Fire

- Auxiliary method for purifying extracts from plant or mineral sources. Goes back to ancient temple burnt offerings — "the most purified essence of a material is driven off to the heavens by the action of fire."
- Paracelsus mentioned it; Rudolf Glauber praised it.

#lab[
  1. Obtain alcoholic extract from Vegetable, Animal, or Mineral subjects.
  2. Ignite the alcohol under a *cooling dome* (or cooling helm). Hot vapors condense on the cool surface.
  3. Collect condensed liquid. Use as is, or perform gentle distillation to obtain a volatile solid (Glauber: "incombustible mercury of the subject") = powerful medicine.

  *Simple example (red wine):*
  - Distil wine to obtain alcohol; rectify several times.
  - Evaporate remaining wine liquid to thick honey residue.
  - Distil at higher temperature → black stinking oil (contains healing virtue in impure form).
  - Dissolve black oil in rectified wine spirit; ignite under cooling helm. Condensed distillate can be used as is or redistilled to obtain the volatile solid.
]

- "Vegetables, animals, and minerals with the help of any burning spirit, not only that of wine, but of corn, honey, fruits, leaves or grass, may be most highly purified and reduced to the highest medicines." — Glauber


=== Chapter Fifteen: Antimony

#hm-note[
  Antimony holds a special place in alchemical tradition. Known from ancient times; named Mestem, Asinat, Stimmi, Stibium (symbol: Sb). Parliament of England forbade its use in medicine in 1566 (for ~100 years) due to deaths from misuse. Basil Valentine's *Triumphal Chariot of Antimony* (~1600) is the authoritative text.
]

- Antimony is the *Mineral of Malkuth*. Earth is its planetary ruler. It contains the rays of all other planets and is therefore called immortal. Its spirit is fixed to the sphere of Earth.
- Basil Valentine: called it one of the Seven Wonders of the World — the best blood-purifying agent available.
- Key writings on the Star Regulus path: Eiraneus Philalethes, Nicholas Flamel, Isaac Newton.

==== Antimony Ores and Preparation

- Primary ore: *Stibnite* (Sb₂S₃, antimony trisulfide). When texts say "antimony" they usually mean this ore. When they mean the metal, they say *Regulus* (Little King).
- Common impurities in stibnite: arsenic, mercury, bismuth, lead, uncombined sulfur. Some believe "Anti Monos" (not alone) refers to these impurities.

#lab[
  *Roasting stibnite:*
  - Begin gently at ~90°C for 1 day; slowly increase to ~250°C.
  - *Full calcination to oxide:* Keep below 520°C at start (melting begins there); stir with iron rod; increase temperature as sulfur vaporizes and ore lightens. Antimony oxide is somewhat volatile — do not overdo time/temperature. *Outdoor work or fume hood required.*
]

==== Kermes Mineral (Antimony Oxysulfide)

- Red-brown powder (like the insect dye Kermes); chemically: complex mixture of Sb₂S₃ and Sb₂O₃.
- Much easier to calcine to light oxide powder because of its greater purity compared to raw stibnite.
- Easily takes on shades from canary yellow to brilliant orange to crimson red by altering concentrations and order of mixing.

#lab[
  1. Grind stibnite to fine powder; set aside.
  2. Prepare 20–30% NaOH solution in rainwater (very hot as lye dissolves — add slowly; wear eye/hand protection).
  3. Add powdered stibnite to still-hot lye solution while stirring with a non-metal rod (add in excess to lye weight). Can heat near boiling. Do alkaline leaching several times.
  4. After 1 hour digestion, filter through *glass wool* (NOT paper — caustic destroys it; glass wool from aquarium suppliers).
  5. Into the deep golden yellow solution, slowly pour 10–30% acetic acid solution until pH = 7 (neutral). *Hydrogen sulfide (toxic) is released — work outside, upwind.*
  6. Red-brown solid (Kermes) falls to the bottom. Decant clear liquid (contains sodium acetate — save for acetate work, its antimony contact makes it extra valuable). Wash Kermes many times with 10–20× its volume of rainwater.
  7. Dry in dish. Use the resulting red-brown Kermes powder.
  - Other alkalis also work: KOH, liquid ammonia.
]

==== Glass of Antimony

- Ancient glassmaking artifact. Formed by fusing antimony oxide with some residual sulfide.

#lab[
  1. Calcine stibnite or Kermes to oxide (not too rigorous — small proportion of sulfide needed for glass formation).
  2. Fuse finely ground oxide/sulfide mixture in a *strong porcelain crucible* at 700–1000°C (sometimes up to 1300°C). Adding a small amount of raw stibnite helps obtain deep ruby red glass.
  3. Check readiness: dip thin iron rod into melt; the adhering glass should be transparent. If cloudy, continue heating. Do not over-fuse (material volatilizes).
  4. When ready, quickly pour molten material into a wide flat *copper dish*. Cool to a transparent yellow to deep red glass.
  5. Grind to very fine powder before extraction with a prepared menstruum.
  - Do NOT use borax as flux — may cause problems in removal and possible alchemical death of subject.
]

==== Vinegar of Antimony

- Stibnite undergoes fermentation similar to winemaking. Result: *Vinegar of Antimony* = pure Fixed Spirit of Antimony = nearly a Universal Menstruum for the Mineral world + powerful medicine.
- Basil Valentine: will eliminate all toxins from the body.

#lab[
  1. Grind several pounds of stibnite to fine powder; roast at ~90°C for 1 day to remove arsenic/mercury/free sulfur.
  2. Mix 3 parts roasted ore + 7 parts distilled rainwater by weight. Seal in flask; digest at 40–50°C, shaking frequently. Allow *up to 1 year or longer* for fermentation.
  3. When the liquid becomes more viscous/soapy/foamy (Antimony Spirit has entered the water), attach to distillation train.
  4. Begin distillation at 80°C; slowly raise to ~400°C over 3 days.
  5. Cool completely; observe yellow-to-red sublimate on glassware walls or as crust above residue.
  6. Return distillate to residue; rinse all sublimate into the vessel; repeat distillation cycle *2 more times*.
  7. Liquid from final distillation = *Vinegar of Antimony* (still a weak solution but excellent healing qualities).

  *Concentrating:*
  - Perform 4×3 distillation to obtain 12 fractions. Identify and combine fractions with the lowest pH (most acidic).
  - Continue distilling, testing, and combining until isolated distillate reaches *pH = 1*.
  - Result = concentrated Vinegar of Antimony. Small yield but very powerful as menstruum and medicine; will extract essentials from virtually all the Mineral realm.
]

==== Fixed Red Oil of Antimony

#lab[
  1. Calcine stibnite/Kermes to oxide; make *Glass of Antimony*; powder finely.
  2. Extract with strong vinegar or *Radical Vinegar* at ~40°C for several weeks, agitating (especially first few days to prevent coalescing). Solution turns golden to deep red. Filter; repeat with fresh vinegar.
  3. Combine all extracts; filter into distillation vessel. Gently distil until thickened; add water to dissolve residue; continue distillation. Repeat washing with water (or alcohol — faster, forms ethyl acetate). Result: golden-brown gummy resin.
  4. Distil resin as in the acetate work → drops of *blood-red oil* collect (Fixed Tincture of Antimony). Collect by dissolving in alcohol; rinse glassware with alcohol; combine all liquid. Stand several days; decant clear tinted extract.
]

==== Star Regulus of Antimony (The Flamel Path)

#doctrine[
  "In Antimony are Mercury (in the regulus), Sulfur (in the redness) and Salt (in the black earth which sinks to the bottom), which three, corrected, separated, and finally united together in the proper manner of Art so that fixation be obtained without poison, give an opportunity to the artificer to approach the Stone of Fire." — Isaac Newton
]

- Advanced alchemical work. Dangerous. Taken to completion: leads to the Philosopher's Stone (summit of Dry Way lab alchemy).
- Metallic antimony reduced from its ore. When well prepared and purified: shows a *starry pattern* on the surface. Metal is brittle and reduces to powder easily.

#lab[
  *Isaac Newton's recipe:* 2 parts stibnite + 1 part iron filings + 4 parts burnt tartar. Fuse in crucible; cool slowly.
  - The iron takes up the sulfur from the stibnite → iron sulfide (slag/scoria) + metallic antimony (Regulus) sinks to bottom.
  - *Scoria from the first reduction contains the Seed of Gold — save it.*
  - *Alternative recipe:* 12 parts stibnite + 5 parts iron filings + 6 parts niter + 9 parts raw tartar. (Even small iron nails can be used instead of filings.)
  - The raw tartar increases the yield of Seed of Gold in the scoria.

  *Purification of the Regulus:*
  1. Break off slag with hammer. Grind Regulus; mix with twice its weight of niter; fuse again in crucible. Repeat several times until *starry pattern develops* in the cooled metal surface.
  2. This = *Star Regulus* (also: *Martial Regulus*, because of the iron used).

  *Balm of Antimony:* Extract powdered Regulus with spirit of turpentine → deep red. Remove turpentine → oil dissolved in spirit of wine → used for pulmonary illnesses.
]

#safety[
  Niter-containing fusion mixtures are essentially gunpowder placed in a very hot crucible. *Add material slowly.* This is why the ancients called this process *Detonation* — because that is what happens if done carelessly.
]

==== Star Regulus Path to the Philosopher's Stone

#lab[
  1. Alloy Star Regulus with ~2× pure silver + small amount of copper → *Lunar Venusian Regulus* (beautiful violet color). Silver = medium ("Doves of Diana") to transfer fixed spirit of antimony into the mercury.
  2. Amalgamate with purified metallic mercury; wash; distil. Repeat amalgamation/distillation *7–10 times* = "letting the *Eagles fly*."
  3. After final Eagle: distil the mercury *2 times by itself* → *Animated Mercury* (fertile matrix).
  4. The residue of silver remaining after distillation ("Dead Doves of Diana") is cleaned and reused each cycle.
  5. Seeded with purified gold; digested over a long period:
     - *Nigredo* (Black) → *Peacock's Tail* (iridescence) → *Albedo* (White) → *Rubedo* (Red) = *Red Stone*.
  6. The Red Stone can be multiplied using fresh Animated Mercury.
]

- *Alternative path (without metallic mercury):* Unite the Regulus with gold through long digestion with a menstruum derived similarly to the Urine Alkahest, in a closed vessel. Same color progression. The Regulus = "Mercury / Our Luna"; gold = "Sol / Sulfur"; liquid menstruum = "Mercury / Secret Fire."


=== Chapter Sixteen: The Seed of Metals

#doctrine[
  "Nature performs whatsoever the Sperm requires of Her. Nature works on Seed." — Sendivogius, New Chemical Light

  "She is One and produces different things but only through the mediate instrumentality of Seed."
]

- The Seed of metals is their *Radical Moisture* = the Mercury of the Sages. It is the *Sperm* in which the Vital Principle floats invisibly. The seed is perfectly ripened in *gold*; in other metals it is crude (like green fruit, insufficiently digested by the Sun's heat and the elements).
- The proper seed placed into the proper matrix is the alchemist's work. Then Nature takes over.
- "The Salt or body determines the Fire or Seed to burn in a characteristic manner... Salt is the Womb wherein the Sulfurous nature and the Mercurial nature unite to produce the Living Chemical Child in which the Celestial Fire incarnates."
- The most coveted seed is the *Seed of Gold* as gold contains the most perfect reflection of the Celestial Fire.

==== The Three Kinds of Gold (L'Hermetical Triumph)

1. *Astral Gold:* Center is in the Sun, communicated by its rays to all heavenly bodies. An igneous substance, continuous emanation of solar corpuscles in perpetual flux and reflux. Penetrates the entire universe. We breathe Astral Gold continuously; solar particles permeate our bodies.
2. *Elemental Gold:* The purest and most fixed portion of the elements and of all substances composed by them. Every sublunary being of the three kingdoms contains in its center a precious grain of this Elemental Gold. This is "the Gold of the Wise."
3. *Common Gold:* The bright metal, considered by most men as the sovereign remedy for all evils and the foundation of human power.

- When Elemental Gold is perfectly calcined and exalted to whiteness, it acquires a natural sympathy for Astral Gold and becomes a true magnet for it — attracting and concentrating solar particles until it approaches becoming the *living gold of the Philosophers*.
- Johannes Trithemius: "The forms in which this living principle becomes fixed, become perfect and permanent. Thus, the Philosophical Stone is the ultimate that can be made using it, making that which is volatile to become fixed."


=== Chapter Seventeen: The Philosopher's Stone

#doctrine[
  "According to Hermetic tradition, the Philosopher's Stone is manifest as a heavy crystalline substance similar to pulverized glass, ranging from crimson to saffron in color. It has no odor, is not combustible, yet melts easily like wax by candle flame alone and readily dissolves into water or wine. The materials to make it are abundant and available to anyone."
]

- Powers of the Stone: cures all sickness, restores lost youth, transmutes metals into gold.
- Modern confirmations: 1960s — scientists formed tiny gold by bombarding mercury with high-energy particles. 1970s–80s — French biochemist Louis Kervran revealed *Biological Transmutations* (elemental transmutation in living systems). Cold Fusion controversy continues. Quantum Physics: the observer affects the material world.
- The perfection and evolution of the alchemist is the *true goal*. One must "become the living stone before being able to produce the tangible stone."
- In the wrong hands: the Stone could multiply into catastrophic quantities of gold, devastating world economies.

==== The Way of Divine Cinnabar

- Uses metallic mercury (very toxic, insidious, can contaminate areas that are very difficult to clean up).
- "All of the laboratory skills developed in the Lesser Works will be called into play."

*Mercury = female matrix; Gold = male / the Sun. Their proper union → birth of The Chemical Child (the Philosopher's Stone).*

==== Purification of Mercury Metal

#lab[
  1. Buy high-purity (triple distilled) mercury; still purify alchemically.
  2. Wash well with rainwater; squeeze through *chamois* leather.
  3. Cover with dried powdered sea salt; mix thoroughly in mortar/pestle. Salt may darken to black from impurities. Wash dirty salt out with rainwater; repeat 1–2 times.
  4. In mortar: equal mercury + sea salt + saturate with strong distilled vinegar (~10% acetic acid). Mix vigorously ~10 minutes. Wash out with rainwater until mercury appears shiny and bright.
  5. Press through chamois (no residue should remain). Mercury should leave no trail when rolled across a smooth surface; no scum at surface. = *"The field prepared and fit to receive our noble king."*
]

==== Animation of Mercury

*Method 1 — Simple Gold Amalgam (slowest, least hazardous):*

#lab[
  1. Grind pure native gold (nuggets or dust) with salt and vinegar to a paste; wash out salt; dry.
  2. To 29 parts purified mercury add 1¼ parts gold powder; grind into a fluid amalgam.
  3. Wash amalgam with water until clean and bright. Wipe surface dry with paper towel.
  4. Place dried amalgam in a tall strong glass vessel; seal well.
  5. Digest at ~40°C for 3 months; then raise to 60°C for another 3 months.
  - Result (6 months total): *Animated Mercury.*
]

*Method 2 — Divine Cinnabar Path (most powerful, most dangerous):*

#lab[
  1. Mix purified mercury with equal weight of *native sulfur* in mortar; grind well. Matter turns black (mercury sulfide / crude cinnabar). Examine with magnifier — no tiny mercury globules should remain; add more sulfur if needed.
  2. *Optional improvement:* Sublime the black cinnabar to obtain brilliant orange cinnabar (best form).
  3. Mix cinnabar (black or orange) with equal weight of *iron filings* in a strong retort for distillation. (Some operators use 50/50 Star Regulus + iron filings.) The iron takes up the sulfur; mercury metal reduces and distils over.
  4. Lead distillation outlet into a container of water. Mercury vapor condenses into a pool of bright shining mercury. *Proper ventilation essential; strong vessels required.*
  5. Collect mercury; squeeze through chamois. This = 1 *Eagle*. Repeat the whole cinnabar cycle (make cinnabar with fresh native sulfur; reduce with iron) *7 times total.*
  6. After the 7th Eagle, distil mercury *2 times by itself*.
  - Result: *Animated Mercury* = "the fertilized matrix in which you may plant your corn."
]

#safety[
  - Metallic mercury is *extremely toxic and insidious*. Never work with it without advanced skills, proper ventilation, and full protective measures. Mercury contamination is very difficult to remediate.
  - When the retort cools after distillation, remove the outlet tube from the water *before* the retort cools completely — or vacuum will draw water back in, potentially causing an *explosion*.
]

==== The Alchemical Rebis (Union of Opposites)

#lab[
  1. Amalgamate *4 parts Animated Mercury* + *1 part fine gold powder* in a glass mortar.
  2. Wash amalgam with water until clean and shining; blot dry.
  3. Place amalgam into a long-necked strong glass vessel (only 1/3 filled). Warm to ~50°C; seal air-tight (Hermetic seal — in old days the glass neck was melted closed; modern precision ground joints are sufficient). Allow to cool slightly.
  4. Digest at 40–50°C. After ~3 months: matter darkens → entirely black = *Nigredo* (Black Stage).
  5. Gently raise heat to 60–65°C. After 2–3 months: iridescent surface colors = *Peacock's Tail*.
  6. Continue digesting → matter gradually becomes lighter = beginning of *Albedo* (Whitening). Approximately 9 more months for matter to become entirely white.
  7. Very slowly raise heat to ~130°C over several months. Whiteness gives way to yellowness then deepens into red = *Rubedo* (Red Stage).
  8. Digest at ~200°C for additional 2 months to mature. Cool slowly; break vessel → *Red Stone in the First Degree.*
]

- The Red Stone: heavy crystalline substance, crimson to saffron in color; no odor; not combustible; melts easily like wax; dissolves readily into water or wine.

==== Inceration

- Required before the Stone can effect metallic transmutations. After Inceration, the Stone is dedicated *solely* to transmutation (no longer used for medicine).
- Purpose: augments the Stone's fusibility and ingress (ability to penetrate) into metals.

#lab[
  1. Grind a portion of Red Stone to powder; amalgamate with *6× its weight of Animated Mercury*. Wash with rainwater; blot dry. Squeeze through chamois (save mercury that passes through for later use). Collect soft amalgam from inside chamois.
  2. Place into tall glass vessel; digest for *3 months at each of the four heats:* 40°C → 65°C → 130°C → 200°C.
  3. Break open vessel; matter should now be easy to fuse like wax and not smoke at all = *Incerated Red Stone*, ready for Projection on metals.
]

==== Multiplication of the Red Stone

- *First Degree:* 1 part Stone transmutes 10 parts metal.
- Each multiplication cycle raises the power 10-fold.

#lab[
  1. Take 1 part Red Stone; amalgamate with 10 parts Animated Mercury. Wash; blot dry. Place clean amalgam in tall glass vessel; seal.
  2. Begin same regimen at 40°C → same color sequence (black → white → red) but *much faster*.
  3. Increase heat according to color changes. After Red Stage: cool; remove from vessel.
  - Result: 1 part now acts on 100 parts metal.
  - Repeat: 1 part acts on 1,000 parts; then 10,000, etc.
  - *Warning:* Do not multiply more than 7 times — said to become first luminous then unstable, with possibility of catastrophic consequences.
]

==== Projection

#lab[
  1. Melt the target metal (e.g., 100 parts pure silver) in a crucible until completely molten.
  2. Form 1 part Incerated Red Stone into several small balls or pills.
  3. Slowly add pills one at a time; allow each to fuse with the silver.
  4. Keep contents molten for 2 hours as the metal matures and evolves.
  5. Allow to cool slowly; break from crucible. Re-melt metal and cast into an ingot.
  6. All silver should have changed to 24k gold. *Assay to determine actual transmutation ratio.*
  - Silver is a noble metal (next to gold) and used as a guide to determining the Stone's strength.
  - The same 1 part may act on fewer parts of cruder metals (e.g., 10 parts tin/lead for what acts on 100 parts silver).
]

#hm-note[
  Historical note: Dr. John Dee and Edward Kelly, having come into possession of a quantity of Red Stone, performed various transmutations only to discover *after using more than half* that the Stone's power was far greater than they had imagined.
]


